# Database Patterns

## Repository Pattern

Each entity has a dedicated repository class:

```typescript
@Injectable()
export class TournamentRepository {
  constructor(
    @InjectRepository(Tournament)
    private readonly repo: Repository<Tournament>,
  ) {}

  async findById(id: string): Promise<Tournament | null> {
    return this.repo.findOne({ where: { id } });
  }
}
```

## Query Optimization

**Avoid N+1 queries** — use relations or query builder:

```typescript
// Bad: N+1
const tournaments = await this.repo.find();
for (const t of tournaments) {
  t.entries = await this.entryRepo.find({ tournament_id: t.id });
}

// Good: eager load
const tournaments = await this.repo.find({
  relations: ["entries", "entries.bot"],
});

// Good: query builder
const tournaments = await this.repo
  .createQueryBuilder("t")
  .leftJoinAndSelect("t.entries", "e")
  .where("t.status = :status", { status: "active" })
  .getMany();
```

## Transactions

Use transactions for multi-step writes:

```typescript
await this.dataSource.transaction(async (manager) => {
  await manager.save(Tournament, tournament);
  await manager.save(TournamentEntry, entries);
});
```

## Parameterized Queries

**Never concatenate user input into queries:**

```typescript
// Bad - SQL injection risk
await this.repo.query(`SELECT * FROM users WHERE name = '${name}'`);

// Good - parameterized
await this.repo.query(`SELECT * FROM users WHERE name = $1`, [name]);
```

## Pagination

Always paginate large result sets:

```typescript
async findAll(page = 1, limit = 20): Promise<[Tournament[], number]> {
  return this.repo.findAndCount({
    skip: (page - 1) * limit,
    take: limit,
    order: { created_at: "DESC" },
  });
}
```
